          <title>Blackhawks' losing streak reaches 4 games after 4-2 loss to Bruins</title>
          <description><![CDATA[CHICAGO (AP) — Brad Marchand and Morgan Geekie each scored two goals, and the Boston Bruins beat the struggling Chicago Blackhawks, 4-2 , on Wednesday night. Boston posted its third consecutive win — all in the past four days. It rallied for a 3-2 overtime victory against Detroit on Tuesday night.]]></description>
